strings.Value: "I must sleep. And don't you dare wake me up â€” even if my clothes suddenly catch fire."
"I suppose I shall bid you goodnight, and depart your enlightened company. I need some sleep."
"This will not do, sir gnome: you may need to stay on guard. Just don't sleep too soundly."
"I remember last time. You snored so loudly no one but you could sleep at all."
"Great! But while the buffoon is away, who will sit here with a smug face and order people around? I'll do it if you like!"
"Oh, I better get to sleep before he does! How is it that some gnomes snore louder than orcs?!"
"A brook doesn't tire of babbling, and Jubilost doesn't tire of lecturing!"
"A brook doesn't tire of babbling, and Jubilost doesn't tire of lecturing!"
